body:
@merlimat @ivankelly it looks like you worked in these file recently, please take a look

@lhotari I think that this fix will make the tests more reliable, probably uncovering new flaky tests, but rerunning a test in an unknown environment is far worse that seeing a flaky test.

Flaky tests can be a symptom that something is going wrong, we should not rely on this kind of tricks

cc @sijie @rdhabalia

@sijia-w Thanks for your contribution.
Since you've remove one file, you need to remove it from the [sidebars.json](https://github.com/apache/pulsar/blob/master/site2/website/sidebars.json) file as well.
You can do it in this PR or in a separate PR, either is OK. Just remember to do it.
